headline: Carnival Says Cruise Bookings Are Strong. Its Stock Slides Anyway.
summary: Carnival Corporation shares fell Monday even after the company posted better-than-estimated results, lifted its outlook and said booking volumes were outpacing capacity growth by a wide margin.

headline: Carnival earnings, demand: Cruise lines having 'more than' a moment
summary: Cruise line operator Carnival (CCL) beat earnings estimates for its fiscal third quarter, but its stock fell Monday despite the company also raising its annual profit forecast. Citi Leisure & Travel Analyst James Hardiman comes on Market Catalysts to discuss Carnival's guidance and the cruise industry's resilient consumer demand. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Catalysts.
